add

public E add(E item)
Enqueues item to this GraphList. If the size limit has been reached, then the next item to be dequeued is returned, otherwise null is returned.

Parameters:
item - the item to enqueue to this GraphList
Returns:
the dequeued item if the size limit is reached: otherwise null.

get

setMaxSize

public java.util.Collection<E> setMaxSize(int max)
Sets the maximum size of this GraphList. If the previous size allowed for more items than this new size, and there are more items in the GraphList than the new size will allow, then enough items are dequeued until the size limitation is satisfied. These items are returned as a Collection.

Parameters:
max - The new maximum size of this GraphList.
Returns:
A Collection of all excess items dequeued when the size changed.
